---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="Services"
  description="Concrete pumping services from JG Concrete Pumping — residential slabs, commercial floors, Pool Decks, civil pours, and more. Dallas–East Texas Corridor, TX."
>

  <div class="page-hero">
    <div class="container">
      <span class="section-label">What We Offer</span>
      <h1>Concrete Pumping Services</h1>
      <p>Our 38-meter boom pump handles residential, commercial, industrial, and civil pours across the Dallas–East Texas Corridor.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Machine Capabilities -->
  <section class="section section--alt">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="machine-block">
        <div class="machine-info">
          <span class="section-label">The Equipment</span>
          <h2>38-Meter Boom Pump</h2>
          <p>
            The 38-meter truck-mounted boom pump is the most versatile size in the concrete pumping industry.
            It's large enough to service multi-storey residential and industrial tilt-panel work, yet nimble
            enough to access suburban lots with standard driveway clearance.
          </p>
          <p>
            This is the right machine for the DFW–East Texas market — capable of taking any residential job that calls,
            competitive on commercial sites, and efficient for solo owner-operator work.
          </p>
          <ul class="spec-list">
            <li><strong>Boom Reach:</strong> 38 meters (~125 feet)</li>
            <li><strong>Pump Type:</strong> Truck-mounted boom pump</li>
            <li><strong>Average Output:</strong> ~30 cubic yards per job</li>
            <li><strong>Operator:</strong> Owner-operated on every job</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="machine-stats">
          <div class="mstat">
            <div class="mstat-value">38m</div>
            <div class="mstat-label">Vertical Reach</div>
          </div>
          <div class="mstat">
            <div class="mstat-value">~125<small>ft</small></div>
            <div class="mstat-label">Equivalent Reach</div>
          </div>
          <div class="mstat">
            <div class="mstat-value">30<small>yd³</small></div>
            <div class="mstat-label">Avg. Per Job</div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Services Detail -->
  <section id="residential" class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="service-detail">
        <div class="service-detail-icon"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="40" height="40" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M2.25 12l8.954-8.955a1.126 1.126 0 011.591 0L21.75 12M4.5 9.75v10.125c0 .621.504 1.125 1.125 1.125H9.75v-4.875c0-.621.504-1.125 1.125-1.125h2.25c.621 0 1.125.504 1.125 1.125V21h4.125c.621 0 1.125-.504 1.125-1.125V9.75M8.25 21h8.25"/></svg></div>
        <div class="service-detail-content">
          <span class="section-label">Residential</span>
          <h2>Residential Concrete Pumping</h2>
          <p>
            From straightforward house slabs to complex multi-unit residential developments, our 38-meter boom
            pump provides reach and flexibility that line pumps simply can't match. We work alongside concreters
            and project builders across the DFW suburbs and surrounding areas.
          </p>
          <div class="grid-2 service-sub-grid">
            <div class="service-sub-card">
              <h4>House Slabs & Footings</h4>
              <p>Standard and waffle-pod slabs, strip footings, pier-and-beam foundations, and garage pads. The boom gives clean placement without requiring pump trucks on the slab itself.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="service-sub-card">
              <h4>Driveways & Paths</h4>
              <p>Concrete driveways, pathways, and hardscaping pours. Efficient placement even on tight residential lots where access is limited.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="service-sub-card">
              <h4>Townhouse & Duplex Pours</h4>
              <p>Multi-unit residential projects require precise, fast placement across multiple pour points. The 38m reach handles inter-unit work without repositioning the truck.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="service-sub-card">
              <h4>Multi-Unit Residential</h4>
              <p>3+ storey residential, apartment podium slabs, and common-area pours. Strong reach for elevated pours without a second pump.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section id="commercial" class="section section--alt">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="service-detail service-detail--reverse">
        <div class="service-detail-icon"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="40" height="40" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M3.75 21h16.5M4.5 3h15M5.25 3v18m13.5-18v18M9 6.75h1.5m-1.5 3h1.5m-1.5 3h1.5m3-6H15m-1.5 3H15m-1.5 3H15M9 21v-3.375c0-.621.504-1.125 1.125-1.125h3.75c.621 0 1.125.504 1.125 1.125V21"/></svg></div>
        <div class="service-detail-content">
          <span class="section-label">Commercial & Industrial</span>
          <h2>Commercial & Industrial Pumping</h2>
          <p>
            The DFW commercial and industrial construction sector is booming — data centres, semiconductor fabrication
            plants, warehouses, and logistics infrastructure are all driving high demand for concrete services across
            the corridor. Our 38-meter pump is well suited to large-format commercial pours.
          </p>
          <div class="grid-2 service-sub-grid">
            <div class="service-sub-card">
              <h4>Tilt-Panel Construction</h4>
              <p>Commercial and industrial tilt-panel wall systems require large, flat slab pours. The boom pump provides efficient, even placement across wide casting beds.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="service-sub-card">
              <h4>Warehouse & Factory Floors</h4>
              <p>High-volume floor pours on industrial and logistics sites. We coordinate with your concreter to maintain consistent placement speed across large areas.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="service-sub-card">
              <h4>Commercial Development</h4>
              <p>Office buildings, retail centres, and mixed-use commercial projects. Reliable pump services that keep your pour schedule on track.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="service-sub-card">
              <h4>Data Centres & Industrial</h4>
              <p>The DFW corridor's booming data centre and semiconductor construction pipeline demands reliable, high-capacity pumping. We service these sites directly.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section id="civil" class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="service-detail">
        <div class="service-detail-icon"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="40" height="40" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M11.42 15.17L17.25 21A2.652 2.652 0 0021 17.25l-5.877-5.877M11.42 15.17l2.496-3.03c.317-.384.74-.626 1.208-.766M11.42 15.17l-4.655 5.653a2.548 2.548 0 11-3.586-3.586l6.837-5.63m5.108-.233c.55-.164 1.163-.188 1.743-.14a4.5 4.5 0 004.486-6.336l-3.276 3.277a3.004 3.004 0 01-2.25-2.25l3.276-3.276a4.5 4.5 0 00-6.336 4.486c.091 1.076-.071 2.264-.904 2.95l-.102.085m-1.745 1.437L5.909 7.5H4.5L2.25 3.75l1.5-1.5L7.5 4.5v1.409l4.26 4.26m-1.745 1.437l1.745-1.437m6.615 8.206L15.75 15.75M4.867 19.125h.008v.008h-.008v-.008z"/></svg></div>
        <div class="service-detail-content">
          <span class="section-label">Civil & Structural</span>
          <h2>Civil Pours & Structural Work</h2>
          <p>
            Beyond buildings, there's a wide range of civil and structural concrete work where a boom pump
            provides a meaningful advantage over a line pump or chute. We handle the full range of civil
            pour types across both DFW and Tyler.
          </p>
          <div class="grid-2 service-sub-grid">
            <div class="service-sub-card">
              <h4>Swimming Pool Decks</h4>
              <p>Concrete pool shells, surrounds, and decking. The boom pump's reach allows placement around the pool excavation without running hose through the work area.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="service-sub-card">
              <h4>Retaining Walls</h4>
              <p>Residential and commercial retaining structures. Boom placement into narrow or deep form work is significantly faster and cleaner than manual methods.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="service-sub-card">
              <h4>Pits & Culverts</h4>
              <p>Stormwater pits, service pits, utility boxes, and drainage culverts. Precise placement where line pumps and chutes struggle to reach.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="service-sub-card">
              <h4>Civil Infrastructure</h4>
              <p>Road-adjacent civil works, bridge abutments, and other civil infrastructure requiring boom pump access. Contact us to discuss your project.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- CTA -->
  <section class="cta-banner">
    <div class="container">
      <h2>Not Sure If We're the Right Fit?</h2>
      <p>Call or message us with your project details. We'll give you an honest answer and a quote on the spot.</p>
      <div class="btn-group">
        <a href="/contact" class="btn btn-primary">Request a Quote</a>
        <a href="tel:+14697044227" class="btn btn-outline">Call (469) 704-4227</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

</Layout>

<style>
  .machine-block {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr auto;
    gap: 3rem;
    align-items: center;
  }

  .machine-info h2 {
    color: var(--color-primary);
    margin: 0.5rem 0 1rem;
  }

  .spec-list {
    list-style: none;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.5rem;
    margin-top: 1.25rem;
  }

  .spec-list li {
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    padding: 0.5rem 0;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border);
  }

  .spec-list li:last-child { border-bottom: none; }

  .machine-stats {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 1.5rem;
    background: var(--color-primary);
    padding: 2rem;
    border-radius: var(--radius-lg);
    min-width: 180px;
  }

  .mstat {
    text-align: center;
  }

  .mstat-value {
    font-size: 2.2rem;
    font-weight: 800;
    color: var(--color-accent);
    line-height: 1;
  }

  .mstat-value small {
    font-size: 1rem;
    font-weight: 400;
    color: rgba(255,255,255,0.6);
  }

  .mstat-label {
    font-size: 0.78rem;
    color: rgba(255,255,255,0.6);
    margin-top: 0.25rem;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.05em;
  }

  .service-detail {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: auto 1fr;
    gap: 2rem;
    align-items: flex-start;
  }

  .service-detail--reverse {
    grid-template-columns: auto 1fr;
  }

  .service-detail-icon {
    font-size: 3rem;
    padding-top: 0.25rem;
  }

  .service-detail-content h2 {
    color: var(--color-primary);
    margin: 0.5rem 0 1rem;
  }

  .service-sub-grid {
    margin-top: 1.5rem;
    gap: 1rem;
  }

  .service-sub-card {
    background: var(--color-surface);
    border-radius: var(--radius);
    padding: 1.25rem;
    border-left: 3px solid var(--color-accent);
  }

  .section--alt .service-sub-card {
    background: var(--color-bg);
  }

  .service-sub-card h4 {
    color: var(--color-primary);
    margin-bottom: 0.4rem;
  }

  .service-sub-card p {
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    margin: 0;
  }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .machine-block { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    .machine-stats { flex-direction: row; justify-content: center; }
    .service-detail { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    .service-detail-icon { display: none; }
  }
</style>
